article.headline: Wagner 64, Bucknell 55
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Joey Mundweiler scored 25 points to lead Wagner past Bucknell 64-55 Saturday. Mark Porter had 12 points and James Ulrich added 11 for the Seahawks (3-2), who have won two straight. Durell Vinson, who averaged 18 points, was held to two. But Vinson had 13 rebounds for Wagner, who outrebounded Bucknell 41-36. Patrick Behan led the Bison (2-2) with 17 points. John Griffin hit a jumper to get the Bison within 17-13 at 6:05 of the first half. Porter had five points in a a 12-0 run to give Wagner a 29-13 halftime lead.
